Commentary: flat length ball on off stump, offbreak, goes back and jabs it back to the bowler
Commentary_short: Mujeeb Ur Rahman to Mahmudullah, no run

Commentary: nice change of pace, a little slower and wider, and Mahmudullah misses the big sweep, swinging too quickly through the line
Commentary_short: Mujeeb Ur Rahman to Mahmudullah, no run

Commentary: back of a length on the pads, clipped through midwicket
Commentary_short: Mujeeb Ur Rahman to Mahmudullah, 1 run

Commentary: flat, back of a length, angles in from wide of the crease to cramp Mosaddek for room. Stays leg-side of the ball and jabs to short third man
Commentary_short: Mujeeb Ur Rahman to Mosaddek Hossain, 1 run

Commentary: down the track and Mujeeb spots him and shortens his length considerably. Slogs anyway, ends up toe-ending it, and it loops in the air and falls well short of the man at long-on
Commentary_short: Mujeeb Ur Rahman to Mahmudullah, 1 run

Commentary: googly, pitching on middle and turning quickly down leg, swept away hard to deep midwicket
Commentary_short: Rashid Khan to Mahmudullah, 1 run

Commentary: flat, quick legbreak on middle stump. Hurries Mosaddek and all he can do is defend off the back foot. He has to find some way of hitting a boundary
Commentary_short: Rashid Khan to Mosaddek Hossain, no run

Commentary: goes for the big hit now, sees some flight outside off and goes for the big slog-sweep. Picks the googly okay, but there's a man at long-on and he hits it straight down his throat. Mosaddek goes for 14 off 23 - it's been a real struggle for him today
Commentary_short: Rashid Khan to Mosaddek Hossain, OUT
Dismissal_text: Mosaddek Hossain c Usman Ghani b Rashid Khan 14 (28m 23b 1x4 0x6) SR: 60.86

Commentary: full-toss on middle and leg, clipped away respectfully to deep square leg. Hit it, man! HIT IT!
Commentary_short: Rashid Khan to Abul Hasan, 1 run

Commentary: Mahmudullah doesn't pick it at all. Shortish, pitching on middle and leg, and he makes room, assuming it's a legbreak he can cut. Ends up ripping in the other way, and it hits him on the back leg
Commentary_short: Rashid Khan to Mahmudullah, no run

Commentary: finally, a bad ball from Rashid. Short and wide, and he cuts it away easily between backward point and short third man
Commentary_short: Rashid Khan to Mahmudullah, FOUR runs

Commentary: that'll help. A bouncer on off stump, and Abul swivels hard through a hopeful hook. Top-edges it over the keeper and there's no stopping that
Commentary_short: Shapoor Zadran to Abul Hasan, FOUR runs

Commentary: bowled him! Excellent bowling, saw Abul stepping out and fired in a yorker, right under his bat, to take out leg stump. Looked to jab that back down the ground, but  no way he was connecting - it basically pitched right below his bat
Commentary_short: Shapoor Zadran to Abul Hasan, OUT
Dismissal_text: Abul Hasan  b Shapoor Zadran 5 (3m 3b 1x4 0x6) SR: 166.66

Commentary: full on the pads, clipped to long leg
Commentary_short: Shapoor Zadran to Nazmul Islam, 1 run

Commentary: short, slanting away from Mahmudullah, and this is all but over. Looks to fetch that from outside off and pull, but he's working against the angle and a bit of extra bounce too. Top-edges it in the air, and it lands in the gully region where three fielders converge - backward point, short third man, and keeper. They basically collide gently into each other when the ball drops into a pair of hands. It turns out the fielder is Usman Ghani - I think he came in from backward point, but I can't be sure
Commentary_short: Shapoor Zadran to Mahmudullah, OUT
Dismissal_text: Mahmudullah c Usman Ghani b Shapoor Zadran 29 (49m 25b 3x4 1x6) SR: 116.00

Commentary: back of a length on middle stump, shows the full face and picks up a single in the wide mid-on region
Commentary_short: Shapoor Zadran to Nazmul Islam, 1 run

Commentary: And he's broken a stump. Slants it in from wide of the crease, a good-length ball that Rubel stays back to and tries to swat with a horizontal bat. Sneaks under and snaps the leg stump in two
Commentary_short: Shapoor Zadran to Rubel Hossain, OUT

Commentary: full on off stump, whipped to the right of mid-on

Commentary: bouncer, Jayed ducks under it

Commentary: length ball angling down leg. Looks to flick, only manages a tickle off his pad towards the keeper
Commentary_short: Karim Janat to Abu Jayed, no run

Commentary: low full-toss outside off, and Rashid ends it with a spectacular catch. Dives to his left and grabs it overhead with both hands, after Jayed slaps it hard and flat. This has been excellent from Afghanistan, a great start to a historic tour
